# Code ownership for review routing.
#
# SOC 2 CC8 (change management) expectation: pull requests are reviewed
# by an owner of the affected area before merging. CODEOWNERS routes
# review requests automatically.
#
# Solo-project posture: a single owner is listed for everything, and a
# "compensating control" applies — the owner uses Claude or other
# review tooling to provide independent eyes on every PR. Document
# this in docs/policies/change-management.md.
#
# When more contributors join, split ownership by directory (e.g.
# /src/lib/accounting/  @cpa-owner  for the accounting-core).

* @chrissoncpa

# Critical paths — flagged explicitly so the owner sees they were
# touched. (Owner is the same person; the comment is the audit signal.)
/src/lib/accounting/        @chrissoncpa  # substrate write path
/src/lib/auth/              @chrissoncpa  # access control
/src/app/api/internal/      @chrissoncpa  # cross-repo HTTP boundary
/prisma/                    @chrissoncpa  # schema
/docs/SOC2_READINESS.md     @chrissoncpa
/docs/policies/             @chrissoncpa
/.github/                   @chrissoncpa

